--- /workspace/dev_diag.py
+++ /workspace/dev_diag.py
@@ -0,0 +1 @@
+from flask import Flask, jsonify
@@ -1,0 +3,17 @@
+app = Flask(__name__)
+
+# Simulated configuration values and statuses
+dummy_config = {
+    "slack": {"API_KEY": "xoxb-1234", "AUTH_SECRET": "abcd", "status": "ok"},
+    "github": {"API_KEY": "ghp_5678", "AUTH_SECRET": "efgh", "status": "ok"},
+    "payment_api": {"API_KEY": "pay_91011", "AUTH_SECRET": "ijkl", "status": "error"}
+}
+
+@app.route('/check_status', methods=['GET'])
+def check_status():
+    # Create a status dictionary
+    status = {service: config["status"] for service, config in dummy_config.items()}
+    return jsonify(status)
+
+if __name__ == '__main__':
+    app.run(debug=True)
